Part 2: GitHub Actions vs Jenkins Approval Gates
ðŸ”„ Conceptual Mapping
Concept	GitHub Actions	Jenkins
Approval gate	Environment protection	input step
Secrets	GitHub Secrets	Credentials plugin
Conditional deploy	if:	when
Notifications	Webhooks	Slack plugin
UI approval	Actions UI	Jenkins UI
ðŸ”¹ Jenkins Example (Production Approval)
ðŸ“„ Jenkinsfile
pipeline {
  agent any

  stages {
    stage('Build') {
      steps {
        echo 'Building app'
      }
    }

    stage('Deploy to Staging') {
      when {
        branch 'main'
      }
      steps {
        echo 'Deploying to staging'
      }
    }

    stage('Approve Production') {
      when {
        branch 'main'
      }
      steps {
        input message: 'Approve production deployment?',
              ok: 'Deploy'
      }
    }

    stage('Deploy to Production') {
      when {
        branch 'main'
      }
      steps {
        echo 'Deploying to production'
      }
    }
  }
}

ðŸ”¥ Key Differences (Interview Favorite)
Area	GitHub Actions	Jenkins
Approval config	UI-based (environment)	Code-based (input)
Security	Cannot bypass easily	Can be skipped in code
Audit trail	Built-in	Plugin-dependent
Maintenance	Low	High
Setup	No server	Requires Jenkins server
